full_text:
Frank, do you think the lack of inter-station noise makes for more solid voice formation from the fragment material, or just that it makes the voices easier to hear (and doesnt make a difference to the formation depth / quality) ?
Im asking as I was pondering what makes the voices actually &quot;form&quot; better from the fragments.
JEFF

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;purplespacefriend&quot; &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  Yeah, the TRF radio has none of the in between station noise, but there&#39;s still a draw back, the broadcast fragments tend to be longer.
&gt; 
&gt;  Where I&#39;m at even the 469 has lots of noise.  
&gt; 
&gt;  F-S
